President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in American Samoa due to Tropical Storm Gita from February 7 to February 12, 2018. This declaration allows for Federal funding to be provided to affected individuals in American Samoa for temporary housing, home repairs, low-cost loans for property losses, and other recovery programs. Federal funding is also available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Benigno Bern Ruiz has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners can begin applying for assistance at the Disaster Recovery Center, which will open soon. Further details will be provided by territorial authorities through community and media channels. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.